  "concepts": [
    {
      "title": "Common chord and its length",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Common chord</strong></h3><p>The chord joining the points of intersection of two given circles is called their common chord.</p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"250\" height=\"153\"></p><p>The equation of common chord of two circles is given by</p><p>${{S}_{1}}-{{S}_{2}}=0$</p><p>Where ${{\\text{S}}_{1}}\\equiv {{\\text{x}}^{2}}+{{\\text{y}}^{2}}+2\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }{{\\text{g}}_{1}}\\text{x}+2{{\\text{f}}_{1}}\\text{y}+{{\\text{c}}_{1}}=0$ … (i)</p><p>${{\\text{S}}_{2}}\\equiv {{\\text{x}}^{2}}+{{\\text{y}}^{2}}+2\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }{{\\text{g}}_{2}}\\text{x}+2{{\\text{f}}_{2}}\\text{y}+{{\\text{c}}_{2}}=0$ … (ii)</p><p>subtracting (i) &amp; (ii), we get $2\\text{x}\\left( {{\\text{g}}_{1}}-{{\\text{g}}_{2}} \\right)+2\\text{y}\\left( {{\\text{f}}_{1}}-{{\\text{f}}_{2}} \\right)+{{\\text{c}}_{1}}-{{\\text{c}}_{2}}=0$ which is the required equation of common chord.</p><p><strong>Length of common chord:&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"274\" height=\"166\">&nbsp;</p><p>We have $\\text{PQ}=2\\left( \\text{PM} \\right)\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }(\\therefore \\text{M}$ is midpoint of $\\text{PQ})$</p><p>$=2\\sqrt{\\left\\{ {{\\left( {{\\text{C}}_{1}}\\text{P} \\right)}^{2}}-{{\\left( {{\\text{C}}_{1}}\\text{M} \\right)}^{2}} \\right\\}}$</p><p>where $\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }{{\\text{C}}_{1}}\\text{P}=$ radius of the circle $\\text{S}=0$</p><p>and $\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }{{\\text{C}}_{1}}\\text{M}=$ length of perpendicular from ${{\\text{C}}_{1}}$ on common chord $\\text{PQ}$.</p>",
      "position": 0,
      "qcConcept": "66a0dd31c03b9dcaf1afe9b4"
    }
  ],
